'''Arthur Vaughn Jr.''' (February 13, 1924 &ndash; January 17, 2007) was an [[United States|American]] [[figure skater]]. He won the [[United States Figure Skating Championships]] in 1943. He was inducted into the [[U.S. Figure Skating Hall Of Fame]] in 2001.<ref>[http://www.worldskatingmuseum.org/Museum_HOF_Inductees.htm Hall of Fame inductees]</ref>
He was the brother of [[Jane Vaughn]].<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |title= Queenie & Co.|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,796140,00.html |work= |publisher= [[Time Magazine]] |date= 1943-03-22 |accessdate=2008-06-06 }}</ref>
